// Bench 3 pure-Rust baseline (inline_never variant). Sky source is
// intentionally minimal — the rust_caller uses WidgetNoInline from
// the test_widgets sibling crate. WidgetNoInline's Drop impl carries
// `#[inline(never)]`, forcing a real function call per element no
// matter what LTO does. The nolto-vs-thin ratio for this fixture
// establishes the floor: what does the chain cost when the inliner
// literally can't help?
//
// Toylang requires a main.toylang. We export a no-op fn purely so the
// stub rlib is well-formed; the rust caller doesn't call it.

export fn unused_anchor() -> i32 {
    0
}
